Week 7 Summary

- Hardened the local backend so it binds only to loopback and rejects non-local HTTP requests.
- Stopped exposing the saved Gemini API key through the settings API and updated the settings UI to track only whether a key exists.
- Improved local settings persistence with atomic writes and restrictive file permissions where supported.
- Removed the Windows `shell=True` app-launch path to reduce command-injection risk when opening configured apps.
- Replaced face-recognition pickle storage with JSON-based persistence and removed committed biometric pickle artifacts from the repo.
- Expanded `.gitignore` to cover biometric face-data storage, pickle artifacts, and local Codex workspace files.
- Added dependency auditing to CI with `pip-audit` and set default GitHub Actions permissions to read-only.
- Added phase-2 CI improvements including manual workflow dispatch, concurrency cancellation for stale runs, pytest coverage reporting, JUnit/XML report generation, and artifact uploads for CI diagnostics.
- Added Dependabot configuration to automate weekly checks for outdated Python dependencies and GitHub Actions versions.
- Added targeted unit tests covering local settings storage and safer Windows app launching.
